result.execSummary:
One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Timothy Adam Chambers is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: 2:31 Defendant Timothy Adam Chambers in court with attorney Liesl E. Nelson.  Defendant Timothy Adam Chambers in custody.  Rory Eoin O'Sullivan appeared for the State of Wisconsin. 15CF203, 15CF215, 16CF28, and 16CF35 heard at this time. OSullivan files 2 amended informations: 15CF203 and 16cF35. Dismiss 15CF200, 15CF215, 16CF28 but Ct#2 will be read in for restitution purposes. 16CF35 Ct#1 DPA to offer the court. 15CF203 guilty #2 with probation; remaining counts read in for restitution purposes. Expungment available upon successful completion of probation. Nelson and Def agree.   Plea Questionnaire and Waiver of Rights form is filed with the court; court reviews with Def.  Constitutional rights explained to defendant.  Exam'd re: understanding of law, penalty and rights. Def pleas guilty to 15CF203 Ct#2 and 16CF35; Nelson stipulates to a factual basis. Ct#1,3,4 are dismissed but read for restitution purposes. Def pleas guilty to 16CF35 Ct#1 and Ct#2 of the amended information; Nelson stipulates to a factual basis.   COURT ACCEPTS PLEA, FINDS DEF FREELY, INTELLIGENTLY, KNOWINGLY & UNDERSTANDINGLY MADE AND WAIVES CONSTITUTIONAL RIGHTS. Court finds and adjudicates Def guilty to Ct#2 15CF203 and 16CF35. Cour finds Def guilty of Ct#1 in 16CF35 but will withhold adjudication of JOC. Court dismisses 15CF200, 15CF215 and 16CF28 #1,3,4,5. Ct#2 in 16CF28 will be dismissed for restitution purposes. Dismiss Ct#1,3,4,5 in 15CF203. OSullivan addresses sentencing. Nelson address sentencing. Court: approves and accepts DPA for 16CF35 Ct#1. Signs agreement. Court: S/W 1 year for  Ct#2 in 15CF203 and 16CF35 concurrent: court costs (15CF203 DNA surcharge only); conditions imposed by agent. apply for expungement upon successful completion of probation; restitution TBD w/i 60 day. $20 restitution  on 16CF28 is stipulated.  Appeal rights are given to the defendant.
Plea hearing on May 6, 2016 at 02:00 pm.
Pre-trial conference on April 19, 2016 at 02:00 pm.

Information Filed with the Court and a copy is given to the defendant  Defendant has a copy of the information  and waives reading of the information.  Defendant enters not guilty plea to Count 1, Count 2, Count 3, Count 4 and Count 5 at preliminary hearing.  Not guilty plea received by the court.    The bond will continue as ordered.  Set for Pre Trial Conference.  Schedule all cases together.

Defendant Timothy Adam Chambers in court with attorney Liesl E. Nelson.  Defendant Timothy Adam Chambers in custody.  Rory Eoin O'Sullivan appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Written waiver of preliminary hearing is filed and the court reviews with the defendant.  Court finds defendant freely, intelligently, knowingly, and understandingly made and waives constitutional right to a preliminary hearing  The court finds probable cause and binds defendant over for further proceedings.
